fileChanges.details:
Remove lines 12-16 which register individual query vars:
  $vars[] = 'per_page_post';
  $vars[] = 'per_page_team_member';
  $vars[] = 'per_page_resource';
  $vars[] = 'per_page_testimonial';
  $vars[] = 'per_page_policy';

Replace with a single line:
  $vars[] = 'show_per_page';

This ensures WordPress recognizes 'show_per_page' as a valid query variable for get_query_var() to retrieve.

ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS:
The global forms.css (line 126-139) applies '@apply bg-none!' to all <select> elements. Tailwind compiles 'bg-none!' to 'background: none !important'. The CSS 'background' shorthand resets ALL background sub-properties including background-image, background-repeat, background-position, and background-size -- all with !important. This means:
1. The global background-image arrow on line 135 of forms.css is immediately overridden by the bg-none! on line 128 (the shorthand on line 128 applies AFTER the longhand on line 135 in the cascade since they are in the same rule -- actually, since @apply is processed first, the compiled output has 'background: none !important' followed by 'background-image: url(...)' without !important, so the !important shorthand wins).
2. The archive-specific '.archive select { background-image: ... }' in Archive.css also loses because it lacks !important.

FIX: Update the .archive select rule to include !important on all background sub-properties:

.archive select {
  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,...") !important;
  background-repeat: no-repeat !important;
  background-position: right 16px center !important;
  background-size: 12px !important;
}

All four properties need !important because the global 'background: none !important' shorthand sets all of them with !important. The SVG uses stroke='white' for the dark archive context.

NOTE: The global forms.css issue (bg-none! wiping its own background-image on the next line) is a pre-existing bug that should be addressed separately in a theme-wide fix. This archive-specific override is scoped to just .archive select to avoid unintended side effects.
